Metadata: Isomers and tautomers of hymenialdisine and debromohymenial​disine

The 10"E"-​stereoisomers of hymenialdisine and debromohymenial​disine were isolated from the marine sponge "Stylotella aurantium" from Palau. The structures of (10"E")-​debromohymenial​disine and (10"E")-​hymenialdisine were elucidated by interpretation of spectral data. The two sets of signals in the NMR spectra of DMSO solutions of hymenialdisine and debromohymenial​disine are due to tautomerism.
